	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Mapper 215 cleanup</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'd like to clean up <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/INES_Mapper_215" class="postlink">Mapper 215</a> by <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/NES_2.0_submappers/Proposals#iNES_Mapper_114:_Sugar_Softec.2FHosenkan.2C_fixed_MMC3_scrambling_pattern" class="postlink">assigning submappers</a>:<ul><li><em>Boogerman</em> moving to a Mapper 114 Submapper 1. Like <em>The Lion King</em> and <em>Aladdin</em>, it has an NROM register at $6000 and a fixed pattern of scrambling MMC3 stuff, but the pattern is different. <br /></li><li>UNL-8237 staying at Mapper 215 Submapper 0, having the non-MMC3 registers only in the $5000-$5007 range.</li><li>UNL-8237A moving to a new Mapper 215 Submapper 1.</li></ul><br />Emulator support right now is uneven, incorporating size and CRC checks, justifying such a move. I'd like to solicit your thoughts before writing a test ROM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


